In Progress. As reported above, various consultancy services were already being advertised; and the Technical Evaluation Committee had their meeting on 29th June, 2015 to study and assess the tenders/tender documents and to provide award recommendations to the Project Board for final decision/approval. 


The consultancy services that are relevant to the issues/target level are:


i.	Economic Landscape Modeler (IC-2); 

ii.	Environmental Economist (IC-3); 

iii.	Bio-physical Data Specialist (LC-2);

iv.	Landscape level biodiversity and forest quality assessment and mapping using Lidar and Hyperspectral Imagery (SC-6a);

v.	Ground based biodiversity assessments (using a range of key taxa), mapping &amp; monitoring programmes (SC-6b).
